dct_title_s: Map of the Ottoman dominions in Asia: with the adjacent frontiers of the Russian and Persian Empires; Published by Jas. Wyld, Charring Cross East. Geographer to Her Majesty, 1843.
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures. Includes notes. Shows routes of Cyrus and Xenophon, and of Napoleonic military campaigns. 1 map: hand col., dissected and mounted on linen; 52 x 73 cm., folded 19 x 10 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
